messages.content: What are Xycuno Oobabooga custom nodes for?
Xycuno Oobabooga provides custom nodes for ComfyUI to send requests to an Oobabooga instance to assist in creating prompt texts.
What is the preferred installation method for Xycuno Oobabooga custom nodes?
The preferred installation method is using git submodules for custom nodes.
What is the default behavior for `control_after_generate`?
The default behavior for `control_after_generate` is `randomize`.
What is the default host for an Oobabooga API?
The default host for an Oobabooga API is `http://127.0.0.1:5000`.
What is the default maximum number of tokens to complete the prompt in the Oobabooga node?
The default maximum number of tokens to complete the prompt in the Oobabooga node is `200`.
What is the default prompt in the Oobabooga node?
The default prompt in the Oobabooga node is an instruction to describe an image featuring the ComfyUI mascot.
What is the default seed used in the Oobabooga node?
The default seed used in the Oobabooga node is `0`.
What is the default temperature setting in the Oobabooga node?
The default temperature setting in the Oobabooga node is `1.0`.
What is the default top_p setting in the Oobabooga node?
The default top_p setting in the Oobabooga node is `0.9`.
What is the Outputs of the Oobabooga node?
The Outputs of the Oobabooga node is the text returned by Oobabooga, not including `prompt`.
